text: Saint George Church Desinić is a village and municipality in the Krapina- Zagorje County in Croatia. According to the 2001 census, there are 3,478 inhabitants in the area, an absolute majority of which are Croats. == Notable people == * Veronika of Desenice, the second wife of Frederick II, Count of Celje, is traditionally believed to had been born in Desinić. * Gaudencija Šplajt, Roman Catholic nun, social worker and martyr ==See also== * Veliki Tabor Castle Category:Populated places in Krapina-Zagorje County Category:Municipalities of Croatia
title: Desinić
